                       {
                           "type":  "context",
                           "block_id":  "3/xfb",
                           "elements":  [
                                            {
                                                "type":  "mrkdwn",
                                                "text":  "Status date: `2026-03-21` | Branch: `main` | Fresh production build: `bun run build` passed clean",
                                                "verbatim":  false
                                            }
                                        ]
                       },
                       {
                           "type":  "divider",
                           "block_id":  "ASKlD"
                       },
                       {
                           "type":  "section",
                           "block_id":  "NeHvy",
                           "text":  {
                                        "type":  "mrkdwn",
                                        "text":  "*SECTION 1 - What was built*\n\n*Public / discovery*\n- `/` is a request-first landing page with dual entry points, destination previews, open-group signals, and featured supply.\n- `/requests`, `/requests/new`, and `/requests/[requestId]` provide a public demand board, request creation, and a detail view with group progress, participant roster, price scenarios, and guide-offer context.\n- `/destinations` and `/destinations/[slug]` provide destination index and city/region detail pages that aggregate tours, joinable groups, and local guides.\n- `/listings` and `/listings/[slug]` provide listing discovery and detail with itinerary segments, price and inclusion detail, reviews, and quality indicators.\n- `/guides/[slug]` and `/guide/[id]` provide public guide profiles with trust markers, reviews, specialties, and served regions.\n- `/auth`, `/trust`, `/policies/cancellation`, and `/policies/refunds` cover conversion and trust surfaces.\n\n*Traveler flows*\n- `/traveler/requests`, `/traveler/requests/new`, and `/traveler/requests/[requestId]` cover request creation, ownership, offer review, and status timeline.\n- `/traveler/open-requests` and `/traveler/open-requests/[openRequestId]` cover joinable groups and membership state.\n- `/traveler/bookings`, `/traveler/bookings/[bookingId]`, and `/traveler/bookings/[bookingId]/review` cover booking tracking and post-trip reviews.\n- `/traveler/favorites` supports saved guides and listings.\n- `/notifications` provides a shared notification center.\n\n*Guide flows*\n- `/guide` is the guide role-home and onboarding entry.\n- `/guide/requests` and `/guide/requests/[requestId]` provide the request inbox and structured offer drafting.\n- `/guide/listings` manages guide supply, quality state, and persistence hooks.\n- `/guide/bookings` and `/guide/bookings/[bookingId]` cover guide-side booking operations.\n\n*Admin flows*\n- `/admin` provides the guide review queue.\n- `/admin/listings` provides listing moderation.\n- `/admin/disputes` and `/admin/disputes/[caseId]` provide dispute queue and case handling.",
                                        "verbatim":  false
                                    }
                       },
                       {
                           "type":  "divider",
                           "block_id":  "wDkr9"
                       },
                       {
                           "type":  "section",
                           "block_id":  "OZwQ5",
                           "text":  {
                                        "type":  "mrkdwn",
                                        "text":  "*SECTION 2 - Database*\n\n- `20260312130000_initial_marketplace.sql` creates the core marketplace schema: profiles, guide profiles, listings, traveler requests, open-request membership, guide offers, bookings, favorites, notifications, reviews, disputes, dispute notes, auth-linked triggers, and RLS policies.\n- `20260312133000_storage_and_media.sql` adds storage assets, guide documents, listing media, dispute evidence, storage buckets, and bucket access policies.\n- `20260312134000_conversations_and_events.sql` adds conversation threads, participants, messages, marketplace events, notification deliveries, and thread-update logic.\n- `20260312135000_moderation_and_public_views.sql` adds moderation cases, moderation actions, and public stats views for guides and listings.\n- Seed files delivered: `destinations.sql`, `guides.sql`, `listings.sql`, and `requests.sql`.\n- Those seed files populate destination/event records, guide profiles, public listings, traveler demand, and open-group membership. Repo-local seed data clearly includes test guide and traveler profile records, and Supabase auth bootstrap is wired for magic-link entry.",
                                        "verbatim":  false
                                    }
                       },
                       {
                           "type":  "divider",
                           "block_id":  "8vLax"
                       },
                       {
                           "type":  "section",
                           "block_id":  "Q/G3M",
                           "text":  {
                                        "type":  "mrkdwn",
                                        "text":  "*SECTION 3 - Commits and delivery*\n\n- Current repo commit count: `42`.\n- Most recent delivery commits:\n  - `464796e` Replace broken Unsplash image URLs with verified working photo IDs\n  - `a0275b7` Point workflow to separate tasks repo\n  - `7cdd08d` Split storefront into site/home and expand seeded content\n  - `713f7ee` Fix page2 order and favorite hydration\n  - `ab54425` Redesign storefront and add homepage variants\n  - `bc280e2` Finalize non-payment MVP integration\n- A fresh production build was run on `2026-03-21`, and `bun run build` completed clean.",
                                        "verbatim":  false
                                    }
                       },
                       {
                           "type":  "divider",
                           "block_id":  "7wr3T"
                       },
                       {
                           "type":  "section",
                           "block_id":  "u2TQF",
                           "text":  {
                                        "type":  "mrkdwn",
                                        "text":  "*SECTION 4 - Images and assets*\n\n- The latest asset pass replaced broken Unsplash URLs with verified working photo IDs across the home shell, public marketplace pages, request surfaces, destination pages, guide pages, listing detail, and shared chrome.\n- That same pass added and expanded public routes as part of the image and discovery fix work, including destination pages and public request surfaces, so imagery now carries consistently beyond the homepage.",
                                        "verbatim":  false
                                    }
                       },
                       {
                           "type":  "divider",
                           "block_id":  "t+wa7"
                       },
                       {
                           "type":  "section",
                           "block_id":  "2419A",
                           "text":  {
                                        "type":  "mrkdwn",
                                        "text":  "*SECTION 5 - What is still pending*\n\n- Visual QA: walk the full app in a browser and verify route-by-route layout, copy, and interaction behavior.\n- GitHub tracker reconciliation: update and close the rollout issues in `provodnik.app-Tasks`, especially `#20` through `#31`, so tracker state matches delivered code.\n- Color palette update: apply the approved teal + amber on warm off-white direction in the next design pass.",
                                        "verbatim":  false
                                    }
                       }
                   ]
    },
